ype":"codeVoice"},{"text":" must be between 0 and 59.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"seconds"},{"type":"text","text":" must be at least 0.0 and must be strictly less than 60.0."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"It will be rounded down to the nearest microsecond."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If the given time is not representable in the given time zone (for","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"example, 02:30 on March 14th 2010 in Toronto, due to daylight savings","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"time) then the time will be rounded up to the nearest existing time"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(in this case, 03:00).  If this matters to you then you should verify"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the return value for containing the same as the numbers you gave."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In the case that the given time is ambiguous in the given time zone"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(for example, 01:30 on November 7th 2010 in Toronto, due to daylight"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"savings time) then the time falling within standard (ie:","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"non-daylight) time is taken."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"It not considered a programmer error for the values to this function","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"to be out of range, but in the case that they are, the function will"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"return ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You should release the return value by calling "},{"code":"g_date_time_unref()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"when you are done